&lt;!-- USAGE EXAMPLES --&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;usage&quot;&gt;Usage&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Modify the JSON file &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;bginfo.json&lt;/code&gt; and put in your variable values with your favorit tool (as example Microsoft Visual Studio Code):
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-json highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nl&quot;&gt;&quot;bginfo&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt;
        &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nl&quot;&gt;&quot;location&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;westeurope&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt;
        &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nl&quot;&gt;&quot;resourcegroup&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;myRG&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt;
        &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nl&quot;&gt;&quot;vmname&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;myVm&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;w&quot;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Execute the script with you preferred way of doing it (as an example, with Visual Studio Code):
    &lt;blockquote&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Don’t forget to do a &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Login-AzAccount&lt;/code&gt; and a &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Select-AzSubscription&lt;/code&gt; if you have more than one Subscription, &lt;strong&gt;before&lt;/strong&gt; you run the script.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/blockquote&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;images/screenshot_run.png&quot; alt=&quot;Product Name Screen Shot&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Copy the &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;config.bgi&lt;/code&gt; file 
Finally you can copy the &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;config.bgi&lt;/code&gt; configuration to the virutal machine or you keep the setup as it is and stick to the Azure default or you customize your own config file. If you like to copy it, find the installed Azure Extention in &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;C:\Packages\&lt;/code&gt; on the virtual machine you did the installation.&lt;/li&gt;
